The paper deals with channel estimation in the 60 GHz transmission environment, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of compressed sensing techniques also suggests a potential fit for the signal processing (cs.SI) category. The focus on millimeter-wave communication and the IEEE 802.11ad standard could also place the paper in the multimedia (cs.MM) or computer networks (cs.COM) categories.
